ase $|\\Delta|<1$ is still an open problem. The\nFisher information also represents the best sensitivity for any estimation of\nthe control parameter, in our case the anisotropy $\\Delta$, and its\nsuperextensivity implies enhanced estimation precision which is also highly\nrobust in the presence of a critical phase.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 23 Aug 2017 17:54:55 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 24 Aug 2017 22:21:09 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-09-19"}
